  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse the <strong>sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661866902588-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661866902588-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661866902588-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661866902588-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1661866902588-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661866909710-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661866909710-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661866909710-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661866909710-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1661866909710-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add the<strong> sausages </strong>to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the sausages are cooked through – these are your <strong>bangers</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661866914675-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661866914675-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661866914675-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661866914675-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1661866914675-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel, then cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Separate the <strong>onion wedges</strong> into petals</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>ketchup</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>in a small bowl with the <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>sweet & sour mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661866919573-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661866919573-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661866919573-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661866919573-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1661866919573-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion petals</strong> with 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until caramelised</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661866924325-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661866924325-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661866924325-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661866924325-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1661866924325-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once caramelised, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>sweet & sour mixture</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until reduced to a gravy-like consistency, then remove the pan from the heat – this is your <strong>sweet & sour 'gravy'</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1661866929242-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
